data.meta_description: 17-jan-2024 - Maria Pavlovna of Russia, born in 1890, was Grand Duchess and a member of the Russian imperial family. She was the daughter of Grand Duke Paul Alexandrovich and Grand Duchess Alexandra Georgievna. Maria Pavlovna was a cousin to the last Russian tsar, Nicholas II. Her life was deeply impacted by the political upheavals in Russia during the early 20th century.
